                    "@type": "Answer",
                    text: "Yes. The CL series is an interference engine. If the timing chain fails or jumps, pistons will contact open valves, causing catastrophic internal damage. Chain maintenance and tensioner inspection are critical, especially given the engine's high-RPM operation.",
